*Call for papers - Special Session: Women in Logic Programming**
**ICLP 2020 - The 36th International Conference on Logic Programming*
September 18 - September 24, 2020
University of Calabria, Rende, Italy
https://iclp2020.unical.it
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

This special session aims to increase the visibility and impact of women=20
in LP, fostering awareness of one another=E2=80=99s work. To have good role=
=20
models is very important for female students and this session is an=20
opportunity to celebrate women=E2=80=99s work in the community. We hope thi=
s=20
will be particularly attractive to early-career women. The session will=20
include one or two invited talks and presentations by women in logic=20
programming.

Contributions are solicited in all areas of logic programming and=20
related areas, with a special focus on applications that are beneficial=20
to society
in the large, and to the role of women in society in particular. Any=20
(female) student willing to participate to ICLP can submit their=20
application=C2=A0 on the site: https://women.acm.org/scholarships/

Submission Process:
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
The submissions to this special session must be made via the EasyChair=20
conference system (https://easychair.org/my/conference?conf=3Diclp20200).
All submissions must be written in English and co-authored by at least=20
one woman. Authors should select the right track when submitting.

Two types of submissions are invited: Regular and short.
=E2=80=A2 Regular papers must be in the condensed TPLP format (template her=
e)=20
and=C2=A0=C2=A0 not exceed 14 pages including bibliography. Regular papers =
may be=20
supplemented with appendices for proofs and details of datasets which do=20
not count towards the page limit and which will not be made available as=20
appendices to the published paper.
=E2=80=A2 Short papers (7 pages in EPTCS format (http://info.eptcs.org/),=
=20
including references) can describe original preliminary work or express=20
a position=C2=A0=C2=A0 on the special focus of the session. The accepted sh=
ort=20
papers will be=C2=A0=C2=A0 published as Technical Communications, along wit=
h the=20
selected ICLP-TC=C2=A0=C2=A0 papers. All TCs will be presented during the=
=20
conference, preferably by women. Authors of accepted papers will, by=20
default, be automatically included in the list of ALP members, who will=20
receive quarterly updates from the Logic Programming Newsletter at no cost.

Keynote Speakers:
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
To be announced.

